{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-15153/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-15153"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["1:51:53"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["Man looks at woman angrily"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-15153","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-15153"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1/16f4075d-3fc7-4721-b6ff-036cc2868ae4","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-07-01T18:40:48.033Z","creator":"Ada ","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Before leaving, Reynolds announces that there’s “an air of quiet death in this house.” He previously <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW246758148 BCX4\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-13358.html\"><u>told Alma</u></a> that a dead house is a house that doesn’t change. He clearly struggles with the idea of accepting a—literal and figurative—foreign body into the House of Woodcock as Alma changes the dynamics within. Allegorically, their relationship may therefore be read as a clash between cultures, English and European, after World War II. For an insightful analysis of this implied layer of the film, see David Hering’s “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW246758148 BCX4\" href=\"https://thequietus.com/culture/film/phantom-thread-review/\"><u>Old Clothes, New Europe: Phantom Thread’s Hidden Histories</u></a>.”&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-15153/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:744.2391520700637,197.63634554140128,352.661972531847,444.1913813694266"}}}]}]}]}